"""Sweep clamp_within_tile_q (p10 → p25 → p50) paired with tq=0.85.

Theory: Clamp lifts surface up when tile p10 tops are shallower than
the quadratic fit. If tile p10 is dominated by AF tops (which cluster
in the shallow tail), raising the within-tile quantile (to p25, p50)
makes the clamp respect deeper tops, so it lifts less.
"""
